Cricket South Africa has suspended CEO Thabang Moroe on allegations of misconduct on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa has suspended CEO Thabang Moroe on allegations of misconduct on Friday. The announcement comes just after Standard Bank saying it will not renew its agreement as the title sponsor of the Proteas when it concludes on 30 April 2020. READ: Calls for CSA CEO to step down Standard Bank aren't the only sponsors displeased with recent controversies at Cricket South Africa. The Willowton Group which sponsors the Sunfoil Test Series called for Moroe to step down. Problems at CSA continue to mount ahead of a special board meeting on Saturday.